jakarta.data.repository.Pageable.Cursor

  • Packages that use Pageable.Cursor 
    Package Description
    jakarta.data.repository
    In Domain-driven design, DDD, a repository is an object that participates in the domain but abstracts away storage and infrastructure details.

    • Uses of Pageable.Cursor in jakarta.data.repository

      Methods in jakarta.data.repository that return Pageable.Cursor 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      Pageable.Cursor Pageable.cursor()
      Returns the keyset values which are the starting point for keyset pagination.
      Pageable.Cursor KeysetAwareSlice.getKeysetCursor​(int index)
      Returns a Cursor for keyset values at the specified position.
      Methods in jakarta.data.repository with parameters of type Pageable.Cursor 
      Modifier and Type Method Description
      Pageable Pageable.afterKeysetCursor​(Pageable.Cursor keysetCursor)

      Pageable Pageable.beforeKeysetCursor​(Pageable.Cursor keysetCursor)
      Requests keyset pagination in the reverse direction, starting after the specified keyset values.
